"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-2024-peaty-china-medley-relay-b1174684.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Olympics  Adam Peatyhas suggested rival Qin Haiyang \\\"should be out of the sport\\\" as he questioned the legitimacy of China's victory in Sunday night'sOlympics 2024medley relay.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 410, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 275, \"end\": 286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Haiyang\", \"score\": 0.9999938624998401, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Qin Haiyang\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Haiyang\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_Haiyang\"}, {\"begin\": 351, \"end\": 356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999077493224039, \"rank\": 9.089819814295775e-05, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In what may prove the final swim of Peaty's career,Great Britain's menwere beaten into fourth by a Chinese quartet that included both Qin and Sun Jiajun, two of the 23 swimmers who tested positive for a banned substance in the lead up to the Tokyo Olympics.\", \"from\": 412, \"to\": 669, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 463, \"end\": 476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9998222463521788, \"rank\": 0.00017723956676214282, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 511, \"end\": 518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.938552059705774, \"rank\": 0.06267712338539103, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 546, \"end\": 549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_dynasty\", \"score\": 0.9669238474506124, \"rank\": 0.026055845119056877, \"text\": \"Qin\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_dynasty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_dynasty\"}, {\"begin\": 554, \"end\": 557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun-Hwa_Kwon\", \"score\": 0.9999795654662782, \"rank\": 1.58791479974828e-05, \"text\": \"Sun\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun-Hwa_Kwon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun-Hwa_Kwon\"}, {\"begin\": 558, \"end\": 564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jiajun\", \"score\": 0.8020135056823948, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jiajun\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jiajun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jiajun\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The group were cleared to compete at those Games by the World Anti-Doping Agency, who accepted Chinese authorities' explanation of contamination.\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 816, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 766, \"end\": 773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.938552059705774, \"rank\": 0.06267712338539103, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the positive tests were not disclosed publicly at the time and were only brought to light by a New York Times investigation earlier this year, sparking a doping storm in the lead up to Paris.\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 1017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 921, \"end\": 929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.9975202023204682, \"rank\": 0.0024859503544041057, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}, {\"begin\": 1011, \"end\": 1016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 6.280898151871346e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the same newspaper, Qin had also tested positive for a different performance-enhancing drug several years earlier but again escaped punishment on contamination grounds.\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1200, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1052, \"end\": 1055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_dynasty\", \"score\": 0.9669238474506124, \"rank\": 0.026055845119056877, \"text\": \"Qin\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_dynasty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Qin_dynasty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"One of my favourite quotes I have seen lately is that there is no point winning if you are not winning fair,\\\" Peaty said.\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1324, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think you know that truth in your heart.\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you touch and you know that you are cheating, you are not winning, right?\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1445, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For me, if you have been on that and you have been 'contaminated' twice, I think as an honourable person you should be out of the sport.\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not want to paint a whole nation or group of people with one brush, I think that's very unfair.\", \"from\": 1586, \"to\": 1687, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But there have been two cases of it and it's very disappointing.\\\"\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1753, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympics 2024 medal table and latest count today as Team GB haul grows  America's swimmers have been particularly vocal on the issue, with star Caeleb Dressel claiming on the eve of the Games that he was not confident that none of his rivals were doping.\", \"from\": 1755, \"to\": 2009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1807, \"end\": 1814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999977485459, \"rank\": 2.2494611054178847e-09, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1899, \"end\": 1913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caeleb Dressel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caeleb_Dressel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain's athletes have been more coy, but speaking after the final night of competition Peaty called on anti-doping chiefs to do more to keep the sport clean.\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2011, \"end\": 2018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9992521488443835, \"rank\": 0.000748410689294913, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have tried to keep out of the conversation until now for the benefit of the team,\\\" Peaty said.\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2269, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But I think, to the people that need to do their job - wake up and do your job.\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2350, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think we have to have faith in the system.\", \"from\": 2352, \"to\": 2397, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But we also do not.\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2417, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Americans have been very vocal.\", \"from\": 2418, \"to\": 2453, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2418, \"end\": 2431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.699769465438993e-22, \"text\": \"The Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We did not want to get distracted with that.\", \"from\": 2454, \"to\": 2498, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I think it's got to be stricter.\", \"from\": 2499, \"to\": 2535, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What I have said from the start is that it's fraud.\", \"from\": 2536, \"to\": 2587, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you are cheating, it's fraud.\\\"\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Peatywon 100m breaststroke silver earlier in the week, narrowly failing to defend the title he won in Rio and Tokyo, andsubsequently tested positive for Covidbefore returning to swim the medley relay.\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2823, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2725, \"end\": 2728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0091135232480182e-15, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2733, \"end\": 2738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9498543091187112, \"rank\": 0.05279303402284345, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 29, he is by no means certain to carry on to Los Angeles in four years' time, but while dropping several hints towards retirement, says he will take time before deciding his immediate future.\", \"from\": 2825, \"to\": 3019, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2873, \"end\": 2884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999835386008, \"rank\": 1.4768025836175963e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think tomorrow is never promised, so why worry?\\\"\", \"from\": 3021, \"to\": 3072, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"he told the BBC.\", \"from\": 3073, \"to\": 3089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3085, \"end\": 3088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"score\": 0.7941190170596467, \"rank\": 0.1346216908972833, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If my heart wants it, my heart wants it and I will absolutely sign that contract with myself to do it.\", \"from\": 3090, \"to\": 3193, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But that may be a long way away.\", \"from\": 3194, \"to\": 3226, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think I have got to step away from the sport because it has just hurt too much this time, it really has.\", \"from\": 3228, \"to\": 3335, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It could have been my last one [swim] here.\", \"from\": 3336, \"to\": 3379, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If my family needs me, they need me.\", \"from\": 3381, \"to\": 3418, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If they do not and they want me to do it... you can not lie to your heart and if the heart does not want it, the heart does not want it but I am going to enjoy today instead of worrying about tomorrow.\\\"\", \"from\": 3419, \"to\": 3621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the pool, the USA came from behind to claim another Games of swim supremacy with two gold medals on the final night.\", \"from\": 3623, \"to\": 3742, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3640, \"end\": 3643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9994570015685142, \"rank\": 0.0005422138297627832, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia had led the swimming medal table for much of the week and came into the session with seven golds to America's six.\", \"from\": 3744, \"to\": 3868, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3744, \"end\": 3753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9929348844787294, \"rank\": 0.004018857658330715, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, world record swims from Bobby Finke in the men's 1500m freestyle and then the women's 4x100m medley relay team saw the US claim top spot.\", \"from\": 3870, \"to\": 4016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3903, \"end\": 3914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bobby Finke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\"}, {\"begin\": 3965, \"end\": 3984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0224522623654991e-14, \"text\": \"4x100m medley relay\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3998, \"end\": 4000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999610286076, \"rank\": 3.890160786069418e-08, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daniel Wiffen, already the 800m gold medalist from earlier in the meet, added bronze behind Finke to ensure this will be Ireland's most successful Olympics across all sports, even with seven days of competition to do.\", \"from\": 4018, \"to\": 4235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4139, \"end\": 4146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9430288263492723, \"rank\": 0.029236453207893708, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sixth medal of Ireland's Games equals their tally from London 2012, but boxer Kellie Harrington is guaranteed to win a seventh after reaching the women's 60kg final.\", \"from\": 4237, \"to\": 4406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4256, \"end\": 4263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9430288263492723, \"rank\": 0.029236453207893708, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/reso